div.div: The prepared images come with Debian 8
and the old Skywire manager UI
Thus, after flashing you will have to upgrade them later on:
- one time upgrade script -> Skywire manager UI

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 406px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.div: The port-forwarding rules must be configured in the
Skyminer router. They are necessary so that you are able
to interact with your nodes without actually being connected
to the Skyminer router but only to your home router.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 406px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.div: As previously mentioned, the prepared images come with an old OS.
We have currently new images in the making as well as our custom flashing tool (Skybian & Skyflash).
For now, you should upgrade the OS from Debian 8 to Debian 9. The following link can be found in the installation guide section from above under 'Next steps'.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 406px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.div: Once the OS of the images have been upgraded to Debian 9, it is time
to upgrade the Skywire software and some other things on the
prepared images. For this purpose, we are providing you with a one-time upgrade script which needs to only be executed on the manager board and then does the rest of the work for you!
Again, you can find the link in the installation guide section from above under 'Next steps'.

div.div: Verify the connection to the discovery server to which your Skywire
nodes are connected. This connection is being called 'online status'. Please note the reward requirement of 75% uptime percentage to be eligible for receiving rewards.

div.div: You need to add your public keys & a Skycoin wallet reward address
to you pre-made Skywire Whitelisting system user account and the respective auto-whitelisted official Skyminer.
These steps are outlined in the official Skyminer guide. The general instructions on how to use the Skywire Whitelisting system can be found in the dedicated Skywire Whitelisting System User Guide.
